<HEADLINE>
FT  18 DEC 93 / Letters to the Editor: 'Imaginisation' runs riot a bit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr A H COLES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Lucy Kellaway's article, 'Are you a vine, an egg or a train?' (November
17), led her to 'imaginise' calling her boss a hedgehog, rather than saying
straight out: 'You're prickly.' If her boss is a hedgehog carer, being
likened to one of her charges could lead her to think she is being called a
disgustingly noisy eater, or that she puffs and snorts vigorously when
making love. Possibly not the intended message.
If hedgehogs could send their own message at this time of year it would be
for people to take care when tending the garden. Hedgehogs hibernate among
piles of leaves and twigs, so please check these carefully before consigning
them to the bonfire.
A H Coles,
British Hedgehog Preservation Society,
Knowbury House,
Knowbury, Ludlow,
Shropshire SY8 3LQ
</TEXT>
