FT  18 DEC 93 / Argentine forces retake riot city
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN BARHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUENOS AIRES
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Argentine government security forces yesterday retook control of the
north-western city of Santiago del Estero, where rioters on Thursday burned
down public buildings, ransacked the homes of local politicians and looted
shops, writes John Barham in Buenos Aires. In the worst rioting Argentina
has seen since hyperinflation gripped the country in 1989, about 5,000
public employees took to the streets in protest at unpaid wages and plans to
cut government jobs. Nine people were killed.
