FT  18 DEC 93 / EU and US agree oilseeds deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
European Union farm ministers yesterday hammered out a deal on implementing
an oilseeds accord with the US in an all-night session at the end of a
five-day meeting, Reuter reports from Brussels. The oilseeds pact was part
of a wider deal to cut farm subsidies struck in Washington more than a year
ago. It restricts to 5.12m hectares the area in the EU that can be planted
with sunflowers, rapeseed and soyabeans. Ministers agreed a mechanism to
protect farmers from price cuts if their currencies strengthen too much and
ironed out differences on a scheme to set land aside to curb cereals output.
