<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The first half of the wool selling season in major international markets is
coming to an end with prices just holding steady. South Africa closed last
week with prices tending dearer. The Australian market indicator edged
slightly lower at this week's sales, and yesterday at 471 cents a kg. was 6
cents down compared with a week before. The Christmas recess lasts nearly
untill mid January and an uncertain market at closing sales will not help to
bring out business at satisfactory prices further down the manufacturing
line.
