bidding Dollars 502m or Dollars 62m above the minimum price of Dollars 440m.
The Malaysian national oil company Petronas bid Dollars 421m.
Monico Jacob, president of PNOC, Petron's parent company, said on Wednesday
the auction committee returned Westmont's bid unopened after it failed to
meet pre-qualification or technical requirements.
