<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Reed Elsevier in Italian acquisition
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Reed Elsevier, the international publisher, has taken its first move into
the legal publishing market in Italy with the purchase of a 40 per cent
stake in the Giuffre group which has offices in Milan and Rome.
Reed is buying the stake in Giuffre Editore, a family-owned company, and its
sister company Mori which in the year to December 1992 had sales of L102bn
(Pounds 43.4m).
No price was announced but it is believed the stake cost Reed, which has
been expanding its international legal publishing operations, just under
Pounds 30m.
Giuffre specialises in law, economics and political science. It claims
Italian market leadership in legal publishing for the university and
professional market. The company has a backlist of about 5,000 titles and 60
journals.
Reed Elsevier's main legal publishers are Butterworths in the UK and the
Commonwealth and Editions Techniques, the French legal publisher bought
earlier this year in a deal worth Pounds 77m.
