<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 93 / Technology: Yuletide greetings delivered by fax - Worth
Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
For those who cannot bear the thought of writing out and posting Christmas
cards, how about faxing the season's greetings to your clients?
Xpedite, the York-based arm of the US company, is offering its clients the
chance to send the season's greetings by fax. Xpedite specialises in sending
broadcast fax messages - where a single message is sent to hundreds, even
thousands, of different locations. Clients typically include financial
services companies wanting to keep in touch with their intermediaries or
travel companies wishing to send details of late bookings to travel agents.
Each 'card', decorated with bells, angels or a snowman, costs 12p to send.
Xpedite: UK, 0904 690000.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P4822 Telegraph and Other Communications.
</IN>
<XX>
Types:-
</XX>
<TP>TECH  Services &amp; Services use.
</TP>
