<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 93 / Technology: UK's most popular technology devices - Worth
Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Ten years after the launch of the IBM personal computer in the UK, the PC
has become one of the top three technological devices in use in Britain.
Not suprisingly the most populous device was the remote control unit - 88
per cent of homes have those - followed by the microwave oven, which
inhabits 69 per cent of UK homes. One in three households (32 per cent) now
own a PC, while 42 per cent of respondents said they used a PC at home or
work. The survey was conducted by Gallup for IBM. IBM: UK, 0705 561000.
</TEXT>
