<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 93 / Average earnings rise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMMA TUCKER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Average earnings rose an underlying 3 per cent in the year to October,
unchanged from September and still the slowest rate of growth for 26 years,
Emma Tucker writes.
Earnings growth in manufacturing held steady at 4.25 per cent, while the
government-imposed 1.5 per cent limit on public-sector pay increases helped
keep service-sector earnings growth down to 2.25 per cent. Both rates were
unchanged from the previous month, but the September figures for services
and manufacturing were revised down by 0.25 per cent.
The rate of decline for unit wage costs slowed in October, reflecting rises
in employment.
