FT  17 DEC 93 / Bifu tells Bank to fight harder
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD DONKIN, Labour Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The management of the Bank of England has been urged by the Bifu, banking
union, to fight harder for new business.
The union says it is concerned that the Bank lost an important bulk clearing
contract in one of the few banking areas where it is still prepared to
compete.
The bank's tender for the clearing house automated payment system was lost
to the Royal Bank of Scot-land.
Mr Jim Lowe, assistant secretary for the union's Bank of England section,
said: 'There are a number of other areas where the Bank has contracts up for
renewal and we are concerned about it keeping that work.
'We are also concerned that the Bank is not actively seeking new business.
Our interest is in maintaining jobs and careers.'
The Bank of England said yesterday that it was only prepared to tender on a
limited range of business.
It said: 'Bulk clearing is one of the areas where we do try to compete as
competitively as we can.'
