<HEADLINE>
FT  17 DEC 93 / Nuclear review will be delayed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Differences between government departments have prevented ministers from
announcing the terms for a review of the British nuclear industry. The
government had previously indicated it would announce the terms this year,
Michael Smith writes.
Mr Tim Eggar, energy minister, told the Commons yesterday that the
government would announce the terms as soon as possible in the new year.
Last March the government signalled in a white paper that it would bring
forward the start of the review to this year. It was originally promised for
1994.
Disagreements between the Department of Trade and Industry and the Treasury
have further delayed the terms of reference.
The Treasury wants a thorough consideration of whether nuclear generation
should be privatised but the DTI is far more cautious about the
possibilities of selling off the industry.
Nuclear levy, Page 14
</TEXT>
